    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Before you begin...</strong></p><p>Get all your ingredients and equipment ready</p><p>Skim through these steps, then wash your fruit and veg</p><p>Note: Equipment and pan sizes vary. Make sure you cook food thoroughly (even if it takes you a little longer than 10 min)</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-sausage-and-tomato-mozzarella-tortelloni-with-dessert/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Now, let's get started!</strong></p><p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Divide your <strong>sausage meat</strong> (remove the paper if required!) into 6 bite sized balls per person</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-sausage-and-tomato-mozzarella-tortelloni-with-dessert/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once hot, add the <strong>sausage meatballs</strong> to the pan with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 4-5 min or until starting to brown</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-sausage-and-tomato-mozzarella-tortelloni-with-dessert/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add your<strong> tomato & mozzarella tortelloni</strong> to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Cook the <strong>tortelloni</strong> for 3-4 min or until cooked with a slight bite</p><p>Once done, drain the <strong>tortelloni</strong>, reserving a cup of the<strong> starchy pasta water</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-sausage-and-tomato-mozzarella-tortelloni-with-dessert/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Peel and slice (don't chop!) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Once the sausage is starting to brown, add the <strong>sliced garlic</strong>, <strong>dried oregano</strong> and most<strong> </strong>of your <strong>chilli flakes </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!) to the pan and cook for 1 min further or until fragrant</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-sausage-and-tomato-mozzarella-tortelloni-with-dessert/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once fragrant, add your<strong> chicken stock mix</strong>,<strong> soft cheese</strong> and <strong>chopped tomatoes </strong>to the pan with the sausage and give everything a good stir</p><p>Cook for 3 min further or until the sauce thickens slightly and the sausage is cooked through (no pink meat!)</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-sausage-and-tomato-mozzarella-tortelloni-with-dessert/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Stir the <strong>drained tortelloni </strong>and <strong>half</strong> your <strong>grated Italian hard cheese </strong>(you'll use the rest later!) into the sauce<strong> </strong>and give everything a gentle mix up until the pasta is coated in the sauce</p><p>Tip: Add a splash of starchy pasta water if your sauce is looking a little dry</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-sausage-and-tomato-mozzarella-tortelloni-with-dessert/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the<strong> spicy sausage & creamy tomato sauce with tomato & mozzarella tortelloni</strong> topped with the <strong>remaining grated Italian hard cheese</strong></p><p>Garnish with the <strong>reserved chilli flakes </strong>(not a fan of spice? Just add a little!) and season with a generous grind of <strong>black pepper</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
